<!-- FAQ -->
<section class="section surface-steel">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-header"><span class="eyebrow">FAQ</span><h2 class="display-m">Common questions on Process Safety.</h2></div>
    <div class="faq-list">
      <details class="faq-item" open><summary class="faq-q">Does SafetyConnect support our existing PTW types?</summary><div class="faq-a">Yes. We support all standard permit types, hot work, cold work, confined space entry, working at height, excavation, electrical isolation, LOTO, hazardous chemical work, and any custom permit type your operations require.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-q">How does SafetyConnect handle contractor management?</summary><div class="faq-a">Contractor profiles, qualifications, training records, and permit eligibility are managed in the platform. Permits cannot be approved for contractors with expired qualifications.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-q">Can we run SafetyConnect on-premise?</summary><div class="faq-a">Yes. Cloud is the default, but on-premise and managed cloud are available for pharma, defence, and other regulated industries.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-q">How does the incident workflow handle near-misses?</summary><div class="faq-a">Near-misses, first-aid cases, lost-time injuries, fire hazards, and any custom incident type are supported. The investigation workflow scales from quick close-outs for minor incidents to multi-level RCA for serious incidents.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-q">Does it work offline on the plant floor?</summary><div class="faq-a">Yes. Mobile data capture works offline and syncs when connectivity is restored.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-q">What about audit readiness?</summary><div class="faq-a">Every transaction in the platform has a full audit trail with timestamps, user IDs, and digital signatures. Audit reports are exportable in PDF for ISO, OSHA, OSH Code, and customer-specific audit requirements.</div></details>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

